{
  "texts": [
    "For a more detailed explanation of tool learning, please refer to Section 9.",
    "Since recommendation models are domain-specific, LLM can leverage these models to obtain recommendation results and recommend them to the users in the response.",
    "In this approach, there are two main technical points: the construction of the tool model and the engineering of prompts to guide the LLM in the proper utilization of the tool.",
    "First of all, conventional recommendation models generally use id or categorical features as input, while users always give their requirements or preferences in natural language in conversations.",
    "Therefore, unstructured text features should be taken into consideration in tool construction."
  ]
}